Blocks.childText: MISCELLANEOUS. ARR. BY W. In SWEET SABBATH BELL. (90.) 1. How sweetly sounds the Sabbath bell ! Its peals like rolling billows swell; It calls me to the house of pray'r, 2. With joy the summons I'll o - bey,And to God's temple haste away; I'll to the mer- seat draw near, CHORUS. To pay my VOWS and homage there.Sweet Sabbath bell ! sweet Sabbath bell ! Its ringing tones I love SO well. Before His throne of grace appear. "Sabbath Worship." 3 There I will worship and adore, 4 Sweet Sabbath bell ! sweet Sabbath bell Confess my guilt, my sins deplore; Its ringing tones I love so well ; And seek by faith His pard'ning love, It calls me to the house of prayer, Rich gifts and blessings from above. To pray, and praise, and worship there. CHO.-Sweet Sabbath bell! sweet Sabbath bell! CHO.-Sweet Sabbath bell! sweet Sabbath bel!! Its ringing tones I love so well. Its ringing tones I love so well.
